<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1968,2028]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1436,151,719]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1968,1993]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Identification.</emphasis>
Forewing length 8.0– 
<quantity box="[572,661,1968,1992]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[674,934,1969,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperstrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villificans">
<emphasis box="[674,934,1969,1993]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Hyperstrotia villificans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is darker than 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1261,1970,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperstrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pervertens">
<emphasis box="[1107,1261,1970,1993]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">H. pervertens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with more distinct white antemedial and postmedial lines and various intensities of darker lines associated with these white lines; reniform spot is usually 
<number box="[425,439,151,175]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
small dots or an elongate dash; outer margin with small, dark gray, elongate spots. 
<collectingCountry box="[1380,1436,151,175]" name="India" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing is gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,719]" box="[197,939,223,248]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,360,223,248]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Flight period.</emphasis>
Late April to August, apparently multiple brooded.
</paragraph>
